{
  "texts": [
    "Litake et al. [10] explored the effectiveness of various BERT [71] models (baseBERT, RoBERTa, and AlBERT) for performing \"Named Entity Recognition (NER) tasks on Hindi and Marathi datasets.",
    "By evaluating the models on publicly available datasets, leveraging the synergy between different languages to enhance NER outcomes\".",
    "Mehta et al. [102] proposed a novel methodology for Hindi NER using NLP and CRF, achieving 90.7% accuracy and addressing the lack of high-accuracy tools in this field.",
    "Saha et al. [103] achieved an impressive F1-measure accuracy of 73.87% in their newly developed Hindi NER system, even without an annotated Hindi NE corpus.",
    "The authors employed language transfer and minimally supervised learning methods to create a set of patterns for the system."
  ]
}